talented GM Jeffery Xiong in the summer of 2015.} 13. c4 Nc6 $5 14. c5 a6 15. a3 Ba5 
16. Be2 O-O 17. Kb1 Bd8 18. b4 {Haznedaroglu,K (2430)-Shaw,J (2449) Gothenburg 2005. 
Here it is most accurate to play} g6 $1 {so that} 19. h4 {can be met by} h5 {Still, 
White must be spoiled for choice with his bishop pair and space advantage on the 
queenside.} *

