the knight on 45 occasions.} e6 10. Be3 {Against IM Arthur Calugar I played} Ne4 
{That game continued} 11. Nc3 Nxc5 12. Bxc5 Bxc5 13. a4 b4 14. Ne4 Be7 {(keeping d6 
under observation)} 15. O-O-O Bb7 16. Nd6+ $6 Bxd6 17. Rxd6 {Calugar,A 
(2206)-Bartholomew,J (2448) Dallas 2015. Now the most straightforward path to an edge 
is} Bxf3 $1 18. gxf3 Ke7 19. Rhd1 a5 {Black can continue with...Ra8-a7, ...Rh8-c8, 
and...Nb8-c6/d7. White has virtually nothing to attack and stands worse with his 
inferior pawn structure.} *

