1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8 4. g3 {This kingside fianchetto is a fairly popular 
plan against 3...Qa5, but in the 3...Qd8 Scandinavian I've seldom encountered it. 
Still, Black should know how to meet it, as White's plan to exert pressure on the 
center and Black queenside via the h1-a8 diagonal is a sophisticated approach.} Nf6 
5. Bg2 {Now I'll give two possible continuations:} Nc6 $5 {Enterprising. Black 
strives to prevent d2-d4.} 6. Nf3 e5 7. O-O Bc5 {Optimal development supported by a 
tactical point.} 8. Re1 O-O 9. Nxe5 $2 Nxe5 $1 10. Rxe5 Bxf2+ $1 {That's it!} 11. 
Kxf2 Ng4+ $19 *

