1. e4 d5 {Believe it or not, you will encounter more than a few players who will 
decline the proffered d-pawn! Maybe they're suspicious of Black's kind gesture? :)} 
2. Nc3 dxe4 3. Nxe4 {now Black has a choice: Another acceptable option is Nc6. My 
preference is for Qd5!?} Qd5 $5 {This is a cheeky sortie that I've employed over the 
years. The idea is to encourage Ne4-c3 and transpose to a main-line Scandinavian!} 4. 
Ng3 Nc6 5. Nf3 e5 6. b3 {This is Bao,Q (2194)-Bartholomew,J (2443) Las Vegas, Nevada 
2015. Here} Be6 {is probably most accurate} ({I played 6...Bg4 instead}) {, and 
after} 7. Bb2 O-O-O 8. Bc4 Qd7 9. Qe2 Bxc4 10. Qxc4 Nh6 $5 {Keeping the f6 square 
available for the Black pawn (in order to reinforce e5). The immediate 10...f6 is 
also playable.} 11. O-O-O Bd6 12. d4 exd4 13. Nxd4 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 f6 {the position is 
roughly equal since} 15. Bxa7 $4 {loses on the spot to} Ba3+ 16. Kb1 Qxd1+ 17. Rxd1 
Rxd1# *

