1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. c4 $6 {Every once in awhile I encounter this move. White is 
trying to follow with d2-d4 (creating a pawn duo), but Black has a convenient reply:} 
Qe4+ $1 {Now every block of the check entails a certain defect.} 4. Qe2 Qxe2+ 5. Bxe2 
Nc6 6. Nf3 e5 $17 {The White pawn is misplaced on c4; subsequently the d4 square will 
be a constant concern for White.} *

